    "text": "Overall, the performance of different LLMs on the vulnerable version identification task varies, reflecting each model’s inherent capacity for understanding and reasoning about vulnerabilities. DeepSeek - v3 and DeepSeek - R1 exhibit comparable performance, and both achieve the best results among all evaluated LLMs. At the CVE level, every LLM outperforms the traditional baselines. Even the weakest model, Qwen - turbo, attains an accuracy of 43.75%, surpassing the best baseline (V - SZZ) at 37.50%. This demonstrates that, under the strict all - match criterion, general - purpose LLMs can still exceed baseline approaches. At the version level, even the worst-performing Qwen-turbo still has an F1-score (70.84%) higher than the best F1-score in the baseline, VERJava (66.08%), further demonstrating the advantage of CaVulner in identifying vulnerable versions.",
